{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e12a0304-a1d6-44fb-9509-f1eb4eee8ccc","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or**, if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp`:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- For xUnit v2 (your current version) -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Or migrate to xUnit v3 -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add** the MTP entry point property to your `.csproj`:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n     <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or directly as an executable: `dotnet run` in the test project.\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `OutputType` must be `Exe` since MTP produces a self-contained test host.\n- `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enables `dotnet test` integration with MTP.\n- If you're staying on xUnit **2.9.3**, use `xunit.runner.mtp`. If you're ready to upgrade to **xUnit v3**, use `xunit.v3` + `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` (and update test code for v3 API changes).\n\nWould you like help with the actual migration of your project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"deb980bd-8929-4b06-9c1c-8e32f6ce51a3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":486,"requestId":"1BC0:349D35:20279B1:2386035:6A03CDB9"},"id":"63fa3e30-b11c-4560-9332-8a7547259701","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:02:59.785Z","parentId":"1db0a63b-467f-4c08-a57e-a1196a4c7245"}
